 Honour pricks me on. Yea, but how if honour pricks me off when I come on? how then?...What is honour? A word. What is that word, honour? Air. A trim reckoning! Who hath it? He that died o Wednesday. Doth he feel it? No. Doth he hear it? No. It is insensible then? Yea, to the dead. But will it not live with the living? No. Why? Detraction will not suffer it. Therefore Ill none of it: honour is a mere scutcheon: and so ends my catechism. 

 WILLIAM SHAKESPEARE




